    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "siege_weapon",
        "text": "A smaller version of the *kickback spring* was first deployed as a deterrent to keep crops safe from nuisance foragers like moose. These larger versions often line walls or other defensive points, providing a final layer of protection before a large creature would breach such areas. The *kickback spring* fires a compressed disk of rapidly expanding air at creatures, attempting to push them back and provide defenders a moment to regroup.",
